name: "Reptilian Fiend" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Liner pen on notebook page with digital embellishments and color.] He looks like a happy-go-lucky little dinosaur, doesn't he... But NO! This bastard has a heart as black as coal and a tongue sharper than a sewing needle! Never turn your back on him...or he'll take a bit right out of your ass!!! ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
